  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Bring a large saucepan of salted water to the boil. Add the pasta and cook until al dente, following pack instructions. Scoop out a mug of pasta water, then drain the pasta."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, slice the cherry tomatoes in half and tear the basil leaves."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the cottage cheese, sundried tomato paste, gochujang and garlic powder to a blender along with a splash of the reserved pasta water. Blend until smooth and creamy. Add more water as needed to loosen."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tip the drained pasta into a large bowl along with the cooked chicken, halved cherry tomatoes and basil. Pour over the sauce and stir everything together until well coated. Add more pasta water if it looks a bit dry."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Transfer the pasta to an ovenproof dish, grate the Parmesan over the top and place under a hot grill for 5–10 mins until golden and bubbling on top. Once cooled, box up and pop in the fridge, ready for tomorrow’s lunch – they’ll keep for up to 3 days."
    }
  ],
